<subSubSection pageId="52" pageNumber="85" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="52.[189,304,255,279]" box="[189,304,255,279]" pageId="52" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,304,255,279]" pageId="52" pageNumber="85">Comment:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[189,1180,293,502]" pageId="52" pageNumber="85">
<materialsCitation country="Iran" location="Iran" pageId="52" pageNumber="85" specimenCount="4" typeStatus="holotype">
The original description is based on a single specimen from &quot;Perse septentrionale&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="FAUVEL, A." box="[1030,1168,294,318]" pageId="52" pageNumber="85" pagination="218 - 253" refId="ref36359" refString="FAUVEL, A. 1900: Staphylinides palearctiques nouveaux. - Revue d'Entomologie 19: 218 - 253." type="journal article" year="1900">FAUVEL 1900</bibRefCitation>
). An examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[431,521,324,348]" pageId="52" pageNumber="85">holotype</typeStatus>
revealed that it is a female. The male listed as 
<typeStatus isOtherTypeStatus="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="85">additional material</typeStatus>
above has a distinctly sparser punctation of the abdomen and darker blackish-brown legs and antennae (reddish in the 
<typeStatus box="[451,545,385,409]" pageId="52" pageNumber="85">holotype</typeStatus>
), but since no additional differences were found, they are attributed to intra- rather than interspecific variation. Males from 
<collectingCountry box="[855,897,417,440]" name="Iran" pageId="52" pageNumber="85">Iran</collectingCountry>
are needed to confirm that both specimens are conspecific. The aedeagus of the male from 
<collectingCountry box="[850,922,447,471]" name="Turkey" pageId="52" pageNumber="85">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and the abdomen of the 
<typeStatus box="[189,279,477,501]" pageId="52" pageNumber="85">holotype</typeStatus>
are illustrated in 
<figureCitation box="[459,598,477,502]" captionStart="Figs 169-181" captionStartId="53.[106,144,1442,1464]" captionTargetBox="[118,1081,178,1423]" captionTargetId="figure-104@53.[111,1094,174,1433]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Figs 169-181: Aleochara lygaea KRAATZ (169-171; Kyrgyzstan), A. peeziana LOHSE (172-175), A. nigerrima KRAATZ (176; syntype), A. tenuicornis KRAATZ (177-178; lectotype), and A. ignipennis FAUVEL (179-181; 179: holotype): median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view (169, 172-173, 177, 180); apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view (170, 178, 181); spermatheca (171, 174-176); abdominal segments III-VII (179). Scale bars: 179: 1.0 mm; 169-178, 180-181: 0.2 mm." pageId="52" pageNumber="85">Figs 179-181</figureCitation>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[189,1155,516,540]" box="[189,1155,516,540]" pageId="52" pageNumber="85">
The species has been reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[569,615,516,539]" name="Iran" pageId="52" pageNumber="85">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[626,720,516,540]" name="Armenia" pageId="52" pageNumber="85">Armenia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[730,845,516,540]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="52" pageNumber="85">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[900,973,516,540]" name="Turkey" pageId="52" pageNumber="85">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING, V." box="[989,1143,516,540]" pageId="52" pageNumber="85" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref35880" refString="ASSING, V. 2007 b: New species and additional records of Staphylinidae from Turkey V (Coleoptera). - Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde Serie A (Biologie) 700: 1 - 64." type="journal article" year="2007">ASSING 2007b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
